---
/**
 * Doctrine — the four statements under the chapter title. The obelisk
 * video sits absolutely positioned on the right; its currentTime is
 * scroll-scrubbed.
 */
---
<section class="doctrine" id="doctrine">
  <!-- preload="metadata" — obelisk is scroll-scrubbed via currentTime
       (see lib/obelisk.ts), so we need duration + first-frame poster
       on load, but NOT the full byte stream. As the user scrolls and
       JS pokes currentTime, the browser ranges into the file on demand.
       Cuts ~3 MB off the initial load vs preload="auto". -->
  <video class="obelisk-vid" id="obelisk-vid" muted playsinline preload="metadata" aria-hidden="true">
    <source src="/kr8tiv-assets/oblisk-kr8tiv.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
  </video>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="doctrine-head">
      <div>
        <div class="chapter-label mono"><span class="b"></span>I / DOCTRINE</div>
        <h2 class="chapter-title serif">
          <span class="line"><span>Threading the <span class="it">needle</span></span></span>
          <span class="line"><span>between luxury</span></span>
          <span class="line"><span>and beautiful chaos.</span></span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <p>Four statements we live by. Codified after years of expensive agency PTSD.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stmt">
      <div class="num"><span class="i">001</span> LONG GAME</div>
      <p>Your project might be a <em>twenty-dollar</em> business card today and a twenty-thousand-dollar rebrand next year. We&rsquo;re playing the long game.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stmt">
      <div class="num"><span class="i">002</span> FOUNDER HONEST</div>
      <p>We&rsquo;ve been the client. We know the pain of agencies that <em>ghost you</em> after the kickoff. So we built the partner we always wished we had.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stmt">
      <div class="num"><span class="i">003</span> NO LANE</div>
      <p>Comfortable at both ends — luxury hospitality that needs <em>restraint</em>, crypto projects that need to look like they&rsquo;re from the future.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stmt">
      <div class="num"><span class="i">004</span> REAL GOAL</div>
      <p>Not the biggest studio. The one founders <span class="ac">quietly recommend</span> when they&rsquo;re two whiskeys deep and telling the truth.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  import { isPhoneClassTouch } from '@lib/devicePolicy';

  if (!isPhoneClassTouch()) {
    import('@lib/obelisk')
      .then(({ initObelisk }) => initObelisk())
      .catch((err) => console.error('[KR8·doctrine] obelisk import failed:', err));
  }
</script>
